Sammy Going South  (UK-1963)  (aka, A Boy Ten Feet Tall)


Adventure


directed by . . . Alexander Mackendrick
starring . . . . .Edward G. Robinson, Fergus McClelland, Constance Cummings


[english audio, separate spanish srt subtitle file]


BAFTA Awards-NOMINATED-best british cinematography 
Moscow International Film Festival-NOMINATED-grand prix


&quot;Ten year old Sammy travels 4500 miles on his own from the Suez Canal
to Durban, South Africa.&quot;

&quot;A young boy living in Port Said, Egypt, narrowly escapes a bomb blast
that destroys the apartment block where he lives. After discovering that
both his parents were killed in the explosion, he decides to travel (on
foot) to Durban, South Africa, to be with his only living relative, an aunt.&quot;

